      <heading>Sun Feb  7 (Shai'tan)   :: Forsaken Skills Explained</heading>
      <slot>6</slot>
      <level>206</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>The following is a list of skills that you will most likely have 
as a Chosen and a brief summary of what it does (assuming I know)

\c03Enh Spell Damage\c00 - Adds 25% to all weave damage
\c03Sliceweave\c00 - auto skill that compares Spirit/Fire lvls of weavers
to determine if a player &quot;slices&quot; a weave directed at them. A
successfully sliced weave will cost you half the casters cost.
\c03Target\c00 - a quest skill that enables you to weave at an 
adjacent room. USeage -&gt; target 'weavename' targetname targetdirection
You cannot add mana to a targeted weave.
\c03Archery\c00 - Like target with this quest skill you can fire
arrows from your inventory at the adjacent room. You must be weilding
a bow however to fire. No exp is gained from killing an archered mob.
\c03Disguise\c00 - a skill that enables you to change your name
and guild. Usage -&gt; disguise newname 'newguild' newguildrank
\c03Dreaming\c00 - skill that enables you to enter the World of
Dreams while alseep.
\c03Dreamlist\c00 - list players currently asleep
\c03Dreampull\c00 - skill that enables you to &quot;pull&quot; another player
from their sleep into the World of Dreams. They have a 20% chance of 
waking when released
\c03Fx and sfx\c00 - skills that enable you to &quot;echo&quot; ie create
an emote without your name at the beginning. Usage -&gt; sfx &lt;string&gt;
\c03Hunt\c00 - an autotrack skill that lets you travel to a player
Usage -&gt; hunt player
\c03Locate\c00 - skill that searches for hidden players in a room.
\c03Mask\c00 - a skill that hides your ability to channel for 100
hours. Players are given a &quot;test&quot; message of you not being able to 
channel at all.
\c03Obscure\c00 - this skill sets the level at which you wish 
players to recieve a message when they &quot;consider&quot; you.
\c03Ogier\c00 - one of the four languages : Common, Old Tongue,
Ogier and Trolloc. Each language can only be understood by people
who can speak it, all others get a message about you babbling 
Usage -&gt; language ogier
\c03Code talk\c00 - skill that enables you to communicate with Spies
who have the skill. All others see nothing. Usage -&gt; codetalk &lt;string&gt;
\c03Shadow\c00 - skill that sets hide and sneak and enables you to
follow a player unnoticed. They cannot group you. Usage -&gt; shadow player
\c03Summon\c00 - summons trolloc mobs equal to your level divided by 30
You can group these mobs and then force them to emote. Usage -&gt;
summon. To force them to emote usage -&gt; order trolloc &lt;string&gt; or
order followers &lt;string&gt;
\c03Supply\c00 - a skill that enables you to eat and drinki without
needing food. Players see no emote when you use it. Usage -&gt; Supply
\c03T_grasp and T_release\c00 - skill enables you to grasp and 
release the True Power. Players without the skill will not see you
do this however those with the skill will see a dark aura around you.
The usage of the true power to weave is the same as for saidin and saidar
Atm you can also grasp the TP in !MAGIC rooms. Usage -&gt; tgrasp to
grasp and trelease to release 
\c03Teach\c00 - enables you to give greater insight to a player 
into the One Power. It will raise the victims flow by 1 in the 
specified element. Usage -&gt; teach player flowname
\c03Pain\c00 - a weave that reduces victims move to 0 and stuns them
for 1 tick. Non offensive weave (meaning you can weave it at victim
and they do -not- automatically attack back.
\c03Room Seal\c00 - a weave that seals the room from players
entering or leaving. Players also cannot target\shoot through 
a sealed room.
\c03Dark gift\c00 - skill that gives a 25% at double damage for 
each hit. Auto skill
\c03Black Arts\c00 - skill that gives 35% extra mana regen per tick.
Auto skill.
\c03Stormshield\c00 - a mana shield that enables you to absorb damage
equal to the mana add * flow modifier. last for 200 hours or until
absorbed max dam.
\c03Shield of Saidin\c00 - same as Stormshield, both can be worn 
at once and thus doubling protection as they are cumulative.
\c03Whirlwind\c00 - weave (capped at 5k dam) that uses mainly Air
</text>
    </message>
