      <text>A suggestion from your loving Lord. Whenever you enter rp you think
will end in someones death, controversy or whatever I suggest you
always take a log of it. Logs may seem like a hassle and to some, 
like myself, and are practically worthless as they can be faked but
to alot of people it represents your willingness to tell the truth
and your honesty about the situation as well as a sense of professionalism
Many a controversy about an IC kill have been ended by someone
producing a log and they stand as evidence to your proper proceedure
You are supposed to be regarded as intelligent and responsible
players so a log will do no harm to any defense I may have to muster
on your behalf when someone whinges to me about how they are supposed
to be able to shield you or something. Its just a suggestion but
if you do have the ability you would be well advised to follow it.
Shai'tan
</text>
