      <heading>Thu Jul 15 (Ganic)      :: Regarding the role of Chosen on this MUD. READ THIS!</heading>
      <slot>14</slot>
      <level>211</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>This is in no way an attempt by myself to take over
the Chosen, so banish that thought from your minds.
Now, in light of Cyndane's post about powertraps
and how Chosen cause trouble. Let me make this
very clear for ALL of you that possess Chosen
alts:
The Chosen are cold, cruel and, above all else,
CALCULATING. Everything that they do is part of
a plot. They do not randomly set powertraps.
They do not go around 'stirring up trouble'.
The Chosen have been around for thousands of
years. They are the ULTIMATE self-preservationists.
They will do ANYTHING to not lose their immortality.
That means that ANY action they take, and plan they
set in motion, anything at all, is carefully thought
out ahead of time and then acted upon in the most
careful manner possible.
If you are interested in causing random bits of
trouble or making use of your code skills in
order to make things difficult for other players
with no set goal in mind, then I suggest giving
up your Chosen and assuming the role of a
Darkfriend. They are responsible for creating
day to day evil. The Chosen weave plots that
involve so much evil that it's subtle, sneaks
up on you, but once it does, it takes more than
soap to wash away.
Ganic
</text>
