      <authorname>Tabitha</authorname>
      <text>1, Acting against character.
2, Failing to log each session and send it in. (contactinfo Tabitha)
3, OOCly behaving in a manner unbecoming.
 
That's right -- OOC behavior *is* taken into account with the possession
of a Chosen character. These are the most powerful people in the game at
this point, they are to be used for plots and manipulations and making
dark RP more interesting - not for personal power trips or just... to have.
I assign Chosen players as a gift/favor/compliment, it is not a requirement
nor a quota I have to meet... and as such, OOC reputation and/or behavior
does matter. This means anything from game abuse (cheating) to player
abuse, in RP or out. You all know the rules... and you know what will get
people angry. Flashing tags on OOC are likely to be a source of irrtation,
just as an example. Following people around or entering RP uninvited are
other examples. It's just about taste, people.
 
If there are any questions or concerns, please feel free to approach
me... I want this to be a good experience for everyone, and a fun character
to play.
 
&amp;RT&amp;rabitha&amp;n
 
PS - The list above is by no means conclusive, and I don't take well
to loop-hole-finding... so don't do it please ;)
</text>
